+++ Cyndro Mantle Aqua Rubble Cinder Mist Truttle +++

Cyndro looked first at Hugar, then at AzureBlade, and then at
Waterworm. He frowned.

"No, I don't recognize him. One second, I'll check my logs." Cyndro
said and the screen blanked out for a second, then Cyndro's face
appeared again.

"I have it recorded that he arrived just a little while ago. The
Cybertronian Fire, which was the old base, doesn't have any logs on
him either." Cyndro reported and then glanced at Waterworm. "I think
he's new here."

He then looked back at AzureBlade and Hugar. "Iron Raptor and most of
the other Maximals are training right now," he told them, "but I can
escort you inside into a waiting room and notify her."


Cinder and Mist arrived at the exit to Maximal City and looked out at
the bots outside. They saw that a monitor was talking to them, and
knew that Cyndro had things under control.


Truttle nodded at Cledar's orders and remained by Rixer. He held his
two machine guns ready just in case Iron Raptor decided to attack
them where they were.


Mantle, Aqua, and Rubble watched all the Maximals go into action to
hunt down IR, and Aqua and Rubble looked at Mantle.

"Any special plans?" Rubble asked. Mantle looked around and frowned.

"Not yet. Lets go that way and stick together. If we see her, me and
Aqua will combine and chase after her." Was Mantle's reply to the
question after several seconds of thinking it over, and the three set
off down a hallway.
